				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I get your point, but all of those things (except the audio part, but nearly everything I say about the video is true for the audio as well) are part of the &quot;rudimentary video system&quot; I mentioned before. I mean &quot;rudimentary&quot; when compared to today's video systems, because back then each console had well defined limitations that affected how their graphics looked, and that was pretty much everything the consoles offered for you to build a game on. These consoles are machines that draw pictures of varying complexities, they do nothing to help you run games on them or animate these pictures over time. They completely ignore the concepts of physics, level maps, solidity, objects, etc., all of that has to be implemented by the programmer.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

